============================================================================

pitch-core is a streaming pitch tracker that wires several published
algorithms behind a single trait. The DSP algorithms themselves are not
copyrightable (US §102(b); Feist v. Rural, 1991; EU Directive
2009/24/EC). All Rust code in this crate is independent reimplementation
or original glue; no code from upstream reference implementations was
copied.

Algorithm references:

  • SWIPE'/SWIPE (Camacho & Harris 2008; Marttila & Reiss 2025)
    — implemented via the `swipe-rs` crate (Apache-2.0).

  • pYIN (Mauch & Dixon 2014)
    — implemented via the `pyin` crate (MIT, Sytronik).

  • Praat-style autocorrelation (Boersma 1993)
    — independent FFT-based reimplementation in `praat_ac.rs`.

  • CREPE (Kim, Salamon, Li, Bello 2018)
    — ONNX inference only; pre-converted weights from `yqzhishen/onnxcrepe`
      (MIT) are loaded at runtime via a user-supplied path. This crate
      ships no weights.

  • PESTO (Riou et al. 2023)
    — ONNX inference only; the upstream PESTO project (SonyCSLParis/pesto,
      pesto-pitch on PyPI) is licensed under LGPL-3.0. PESTO weights have
      no separate license declared upstream; users redistributing exported
      ONNX should treat them as LGPL-3.0 unless upstream clarifies. This
      crate ships no weights.

  • SwiftF0 (Lemonfold)
    — ONNX inference only; upstream model is MIT. This crate ships no
      weights.

